                <dc:creator rdf:resource="https://id.rijksmuseum.nl/2103429" />
                <dc:description xml:lang="en">Rembrandt travelled to Rotterdam to portray the brewing couple Haesje van Cleyburg and Dirck Pesser, who were part of the city’s Remonstrant elite. While at first glance her attire may seem modest, in reality it was quite lavish. The millstone collar around her neck was a very expensive accessory, requiring as much as fifteen metres of fabric.</dc:description>
                <dc:description xml:lang="nl">Rembrandt reisde af naar Rotterdam en portretteerde daar het brouwersechtpaar Haesje van Cleyburg en Dirck Pesser. Ze behoorden tot de Remonstrantse elite van de stad. Op het eerste gezicht lijkt Van Cleyburg sober gekleed, maar ze is zeker deftig: de molensteenkraag was heel kostbaar. Er was veel stof voor nodig, soms wel vijftien meter.</dc:description>
