                <ns5:provenance xml:lang="en">Commissioned by or for Haesje van Cleyburgh (1583-1641), Rotterdam; ? her daughter, Maria Dircksdr Pesser (?-1675), Rotterdam; ? her husband Reynier Dircksz van der Wolff (1608-79), Rotterdam; ? his daughter, Anna van der Wolff (?-1704), Rotterdam; ? her daughter, Anna van der Linden (1670-1729) and her husband, Wolfgang Abraham, Baron van Gersdorff (1662-1719), The Hague;{There is a wax seal with the Gersdorff coat-of-arms on the reverse.} …; collection Arthur Fitzgerald Kinnaird (1847-1923), 11th Lord Kinnaird, Rossie Priory, Scotland, by 1883, until the 1970s;{Von Bode 1883, pp. 405, 592, no. 260; Van Thiel 1989, p. 224.}…; from a foreign foundation, fl. 10,000,000, to the museum, as a gift from the Stichting Jublieumfonds Rijksmuseum to mark the centenary of the Rijksmuseum building, with support from the Vereniging Rembrandt, the Rijksmuseum-Stichting, the Prins Bernhard Fonds, the Algemene Loterij Nederland, and various Dutch businesses and individuals, 1985</ns5:provenance>
